<br>
The difference between the two is 100% in features that Pro has that Home doesn't. To wit:<br>
<br>
Pro supports up to 2 processors. Home does not.<br>
Pro supports NetBEUI. Home does not without installing a 100mb patch.<br>
Pro supports displaying east Asian languages. Home does not without installing a 120mb patch.<br>
Pro supports logging in to NT Domains. Home does not.<br>
Pro comes with the remote-control server. Home does not.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
Anybody else think of something I've missed? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub41.ezboard.com/bvazaellecommunitycenter.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ammelen>Ammelen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>I Live Here</span><br>  Posts: 1897<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(8/23/03 6:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub41.ezboard.com/fvazaellecommunitycenterfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=179.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Upgrading to WinXP</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr> Never said it was faster, just more stable (than 2k).<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
